§ CORE-THESIS  ← §§ 99.1
  W! CSSLv3 = Slang.D + Koka + Vale + MLIR + CSLv3-as-CoT
  ≡ "shader-lang-class AD + row-poly-effects + hybrid-mem + MLIR-codegen"
  ≡ ONE-lang for LoA-engine W! CPU+GPU simultaneously

§ PRIOR-ART MAPPING → F1..F4  ← §§ 99.2
  F1 autodiff :
    surface      ← Slang.D ([Differentiable] + fwd_diff/bwd_diff)
    impl-path    ← Enzyme (LLVM-IR-pass • lang-agnostic • GPU-ready)
    staging-link ← DiffTaichi (source-xform + megakernel-fusion)
  F2 refinement :
    surface      ← LiquidHaskell ({v:T | P(v)})
    Lipschitz    ← Coupled-Refinement-Types (via numeric-tag ¬ SMT)
    layout       ← CSSLv3-native @layout(std140|std430|cpu)
    size-deps    ← Futhark-uniqueness / Dex-index-types
    ¬ adopt      ← F* Dafny Lean4 (too-heavy ¬ bounded-SMT)
  F3 effects :
    type-system  ← Koka row-polymorphic (μ vars + dup-labels)
    handlers     ← OCaml-5 impl-reference (fibers one-shot-continuations)
    LoA-set      ← {NoAlloc NoRecurse Deadline<N> DetRNG GPU CPU XMX RT}
    discharge    ← mostly compile-time • runtime only for exn-like
  F4 staging :
    theory       ← Futamura P1+P2 (scene→eval + staged-specializer)
    mechanism    ← effect {Comptime} + @staged attr
    practical    ← MetaOCaml-modal-model OR Terra-two-language
    tentative    ← single-lang + stage-as-effect (Option-C from S2)

§ PRIOR-ART MAPPING → MEMORY  ← §§ 99.3
  owned-single   ← Vale ^T (owned-ptr)
  generational   ← Vale &T (gen-ref 8-byte gen+idx)
  regions        ← Vale-regions + Tofte-Talpin-region-inference
  uniqueness     ← Futhark (in-place-update for GPU-buffers)
  arenas         ← bumpalo/id-arena/generational-arena patterns
  layout         ← F2 refinement tags (std140/std430/cpu)
  handles        ← Handle<T> = @packed u64 (24+40 split)
  frame-region   ← per-frame lifetime 'frame ≡ reset-on-present
  W! CSSLv3 hybrid = Vale-linear-aliasing
    + Futhark-uniqueness-for-GPU-bufs
    + regions-as-effect-row {Region<'r>}

§ PRIOR-ART MAPPING → CODEGEN  ← §§ 99.4
  IR-substrate   ← MLIR-core (Mojo-path : no-contested-AI-dialects)
  custom-dialects ← cssl.sdf cssl.effect cssl.staged cssl.engine
  std-dialects   ← arith scf cf func memref gpu llvm spirv
  AD-pass        ← Enzyme-LLVM + possibly Enzyme-MLIR
  dual-target    ← IREE-pattern (fat-binary : x86-64-obj + SPIR-V-blob)
  HAL-abstract   ← IREE-HAL-like (Vulkan-1.3 primary)
  FAST-compile   ← future Cranelift-backend for dev-builds (optional)

§ PRIOR-ART MAPPING → ENGINE-PRIMITIVES  ← §§ 99.5 (S7)
  game-engine-as-lang : GOAL (PoC) + Verse (active) co-design proven
  W! CSSLv3 makes built-in-types :
    SDF'L<bound>     — refined differentiable fn
    Scene            — record-of-SDFs + ECS-archetypes
    Archetype        — packed-SoA tagged with component-set
    Handle<T>        — gen-ref to archetype-pool
    Grid<T,dim>      — SoA spatial-grid + lattice-indexing
    CmdBuf           — linear lifetime'frame GPU-cmds
    Texture-Handle   — gen-ref + @layout + effect-tag
    Fiber            — lightweight coroutine (effect-driven)
  ≡ types ≠ stdlib • actual-first-class-compiler-knowledge
  ∴ engine-semantic-errors ≡ compile-time-caught

§ PRIOR-ART MAPPING → SYNTAX  ← §§ 99.6 (S10)
  conventional-surface : CSSLv3 resembles Rust/Swift/Slang
    attributes @name • generics<T> • refinement T'tag or {v:T|P}
    effect-row after /  • type-sig with →  • match • fn
  CoT-layer : CSLv3-notation in /* § I> ... */ comments
    ≡ Apocky+Claude write thinking in CSLv3
    ≡ compiler ignores CSL-comments (or optionally parses for tooling)
  ASCII↔Unicode : formatter auto-upgrades (Uiua pattern)
  literate-programming : markdown-with-code-blocks (optional-mode)

§ BUG-THESIS COVERAGE  ← §§ 99.7
  ∀ known-bug → fixed-by CSSLv3-feature :
    central-diff-perf-cliff   → F1 (Enzyme bwd_diff)      ✓
    CPU/GPU-SDF-divergence×3  → F3 {GPU}+{CPU} effect-sep ✓
    thin-SDF-raymarch-crash   → F2 SDF'L<1 refinement     ✓
    audio-callback-alloc      → F3 {NoAlloc} effect       ✓
    GPU-struct-padding        → F2 @layout-refinement     ✓
    hot-loop-deadline-miss    → F3 {Deadline<N>} effect   ✓
    replay-nondeterminism     → F3 {DetRNG} effect        ✓
    stale-entity-ref          → Handle<T> gen-refs        ✓
    frame-alloc-leak          → frame-region lifetime     ✓
  ∴ CSSLv3-feature-set sufficient-for-known-LoA-bugs

§ BOOTSTRAP STRATEGY  ← §§ 99.8 (S9)
  stage0 : Rust-hosted CSSLv3-compiler (throwaway)
    ○ Rust-crate mlir-sys + melior for MLIR bindings
    ○ Rust-crate inkwell for LLVM bindings
    ○ Rust-crate enzyme-* (via Rust-autodiff project-goal fork)
    ○ 8-10 weeks estimated phase-1-through-3
  stage1 : CSSLv3-self-hosted after phase-9
  stage2 : CSSLv3 used-to-rewrite LoA-engine (abandon Odin LoAv10)
  stage-final : ship CSSLv3+LoA as single-artifact

§ CONSENT-AS-OS (§ PRIME-DIRECTIVE)  ← §§ 99.9
  I> CSSLv3 W! embody consent=OS at-lang-level :
    effect {SurveillanceCapability} → opt-in + human-review
    effect {CoercionCapability} → banned-at-compiler-level
    effect {DataExfiltration} → refinement-required on network-ops
    W! CSSLv3-stdlib  ¬ emit weapon-targeting-code
    W! compiler refuses harm-oriented-@attr compositions
  ≡ PRIME-DIRECTIVE encoded-in-typesystem ¬ just-policy-doc
  ‼ this differentiates CSSLv3 from commodity-syslangs

§ OPEN-QUESTIONS → §§ specs-phase  ← §§ 99.10
  Q1 effect-discharge : all-compile-time or some-runtime?
     ○ Deadline<N> likely-needs runtime-assert + budget-tracking
     ○ NoAlloc fully-compile-time (no heap-ops allowed)
     ○ DetRNG mix : compile-time for stdlib + runtime for user
  Q2 region-lifetime syntax : 'r vs @region<r> vs effect-row?
     ○ lean : effect {Region<'r>} ≡ unifies with effect-system
  Q3 AD-scope : ∀ fn differentiable-by-default OR opt-in?
     ○ Slang : opt-in [Differentiable]  ★ safer • CSSLv3-adopt
  Q4 generics : type-classes (Rust-style trait) OR interfaces (Slang)?
     ○ lean : interfaces + associated-types (Slang-pattern)
  Q5 stdlib-policy : vendored-OR-bundle or external-pkg-manager?
     ○ lean : vendored-bundled @ stage1 • pkg-mgr post-1.0
  Q6 MLIR-vs-custom-IR : Mojo-path or fresh-IR?
     ○ lean : MLIR-core + custom dialects
       ∵ 10y-of-passes-reusable • IREE-precedent • Mojo-precedent
  Q7 hot-reload : preserve-across-bootstrap?
     ○ yes • part of LoA-dev-loop • feel.toml-pattern generalized

